{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require NHS use an \"opt-in\" system to use patient data for planning or research",
        "additional_details": "To enable informed consent, the NHS should be required to:\r\n \r\n1- Inform patients exactly who may be using their data.\r\n2- Explain what exactly any research is for\r\n3- Provide assurances that data won't be used for any other research, or be shared or sold.",
        "background": "The NHS has introduced an \"opt-out\" system to enable patients to opt out from their data being sued for research or planning purposes. We want the NHS to be required to implement an \"opt-in\" system, so patients are required to give active consent to their data being used for planning or research.",
